WEBVTT

00:03.437 --> 00:04.772
[ Indistinct talking,
cellphone ringing ]

00:04.805 --> 00:06.307
-I'm dropping her off early.
-I didn't even say hello.

00:06.340 --> 00:07.508
I heard your mouth open.

00:07.541 --> 00:08.976
We're ahead of schedule.

00:09.009 --> 00:11.112
How can you be ahead of schedule
on a day at the aquarium?

00:11.145 --> 00:12.980
Well, the fish
weren't bringing it.

00:13.013 --> 00:15.283
[ Tapping ]
We've already seen you swim.

00:15.316 --> 00:16.884
Do something else.

00:17.918 --> 00:19.387
All right, we're done here.

00:19.420 --> 00:20.988
Can't you drop off
Graham first?

00:21.021 --> 00:22.990
I drop off
in alphabetical order.

00:23.023 --> 00:24.825
"Cooper"
comes before "D'Amato."

00:24.858 --> 00:26.360
My last name is Banks.

00:26.394 --> 00:28.129
Well, you can't drop off
Sophie yet

00:28.162 --> 00:30.298
because I...
haven't had time...

00:30.331 --> 00:31.799
to water the plants!

00:31.832 --> 00:33.867
And I can't water the plants
when Sophie's here.

00:33.901 --> 00:35.136
So, figure it out!

00:35.169 --> 00:36.804
Goodbye.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

00:36.837 --> 00:38.939
I fooled him.
For an hour or two.

00:38.972 --> 00:40.341
But you should probably go.

00:40.374 --> 00:42.743
Sophie's coming home?
I'm definite gonna go.

00:42.776 --> 00:44.778
I don't like seeing clients
outside of the office.

00:44.812 --> 00:47.581
You call them clients?
But you're so good with kids.

00:47.615 --> 00:50.017
Only when they're sick
and the power dynamic is clear.

00:50.050 --> 00:51.885
With a healthy kid,
I don't know what to say.

00:51.919 --> 00:52.886
Mm.

00:52.920 --> 00:54.522
Sophie, I...

00:54.555 --> 00:56.690
I know we haven't known
each other for that long,

00:56.724 --> 01:00.728
and please forgive me
if this seems insensitive,

01:00.761 --> 01:04.532
but is it hard for you
to watch your dad water plants?

01:04.565 --> 01:05.866
No.

01:05.899 --> 01:08.536
Next stop,
your house.

01:08.569 --> 01:09.570
[ Tires squeal ]

01:10.771 --> 01:12.540
[ Indistinct talking ]

01:12.573 --> 01:16.744
**

01:16.777 --> 01:19.247
[ Engine revs ]

01:19.280 --> 01:21.014
Change of plans.
I'm now dropping off

01:21.048 --> 01:23.851
in order of
projected career earnings.

01:23.884 --> 01:26.320
Graham, since you're the only
future white male in the car,

01:26.354 --> 01:28.322
you'll be first.
-Yes!

01:28.356 --> 01:30.591
-Are you kidding me?! Stop!
-Gosh!
-What?

01:30.624 --> 01:33.661
Sorry, everyone else.
The world is an unfair place.

01:33.694 --> 01:36.464
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:38.899 --> 01:40.368
Poppy: Ooh!

01:40.401 --> 01:42.370
New drama teacher
already feeling his oats.

01:42.403 --> 01:43.371
"Grease." [ Chuckles ]

01:43.404 --> 01:45.373
Can't wait to see
7-year-olds

01:45.406 --> 01:46.874
tackle Rizzo's
pregnancy scare.

01:46.907 --> 01:48.041
Well, Rory will be

01:48.075 --> 01:49.943
a transcendent Danny Zuko.

01:49.977 --> 01:51.579
Last year, when I saw him step

01:51.612 --> 01:53.013
on stage as Captain von Trapp,

01:53.046 --> 01:54.081
I knew I could just sit back,

01:54.114 --> 01:55.316
relax, and enjoy the ride

01:55.349 --> 01:57.084
because I was in the hands
of a master.

01:57.117 --> 01:58.519
Don't get me started
on Graham.

01:58.552 --> 02:00.921
Nazi 12 and Nun 13?

02:00.954 --> 02:02.423
Talk about a utility player.

02:02.456 --> 02:03.657
What was his line, again?

02:03.691 --> 02:05.058
He had two -- "Look!"

02:05.092 --> 02:06.960
and [wavering] "Maria?"

02:06.994 --> 02:08.629
Well, the girls
are building sets.

02:08.662 --> 02:10.531
They just drew
a papier-mâché
Greased Lightnin'

02:10.564 --> 02:11.899
that looks street legal.

02:11.932 --> 02:13.234
I'm afraid of my children.

02:14.868 --> 02:15.669
-Whoa!
-Wow!

02:15.703 --> 02:17.305
-I hate it.
-Me too.

02:17.338 --> 02:18.972
Screw papier-mâché!

02:19.006 --> 02:20.741
We need a real car.

02:20.774 --> 02:23.477
Who has a car so crappy
we can just --

02:23.511 --> 02:24.878
[ Engine sputters ]
Forward!
I want you to go forward!

02:24.912 --> 02:26.880
[ Tires screech, horn plays
"Yankee Doodle Dandy" ]

02:28.115 --> 02:30.584
Whoa!

02:30.618 --> 02:32.085
Douglas! Big boy.

02:32.119 --> 02:33.621
[ Chuckles ] Thank you

02:33.654 --> 02:36.224
with regards
to my time management

02:36.257 --> 02:38.259
vis-à-vis watering the plants.

02:38.292 --> 02:40.261
You guys know I'm sleeping
with Dr. Dewan, huh?

02:40.294 --> 02:41.094
-Yeah.
-Yes.
-Of course.

02:41.128 --> 02:42.263
What are we
talking about?

02:42.296 --> 02:44.131
Will, how was it having sex

02:44.164 --> 02:45.633
for the first time...

02:45.666 --> 02:48.269
in half...a...decade?

02:48.302 --> 02:50.003
It's been...

02:50.037 --> 02:51.739
dehydrating.

02:51.772 --> 02:53.707
Word.
That's why I've been doing
so much eye drops.

02:53.741 --> 02:55.409
But also, it's so fun,
and I never want to stop.

02:55.443 --> 02:56.510
Nice.

02:56.544 --> 02:57.978
But I'm not ready
to tell Sophie yet.

02:58.011 --> 02:59.913
And I-I-I'm so bad
at hiding it from her.

02:59.947 --> 03:01.949
Yesterday freaked me out.

03:01.982 --> 03:03.451
Yeah, well, close calls are
a part of being a single parent.

03:03.484 --> 03:05.253
We've all had 'em.

03:05.286 --> 03:06.887
Choir practice
was cancelled.

03:06.920 --> 03:09.223
I know. Got your message.
Be right in.

03:09.257 --> 03:15.128
**

03:15.162 --> 03:17.498
And one time,
I had to "E.T." a guy.

03:17.531 --> 03:19.132
Made him sit in Graham's
stuffed animal closet

03:19.166 --> 03:20.634
for two hours
without moving.

03:20.668 --> 03:22.403
So, there are
a few techniques.

03:22.436 --> 03:24.137
No. There's only
one technique.

03:24.171 --> 03:25.138
Lie.

03:25.172 --> 03:26.540
Always lie.

03:26.574 --> 03:28.342
We're home, Dad!
We're home!

03:28.376 --> 03:29.843
Girls, uh...

03:29.877 --> 03:31.512
meet my sister Gail.

03:31.545 --> 03:32.246
Yay!

03:32.280 --> 03:34.315
We have
an Aunt Gail!

03:34.348 --> 03:36.850
Oh, Aunt Gail could go
all night.

03:36.884 --> 03:38.586
Lie, Will.
It's the only way.

03:38.619 --> 03:39.887
Not for me, okay?

03:39.920 --> 03:41.989
Sophie and I have
a very transparent relationship.

03:42.022 --> 03:44.258
I've never lied to her,
and I never will. Watch this.

03:44.292 --> 03:46.360
Sophie!
Ask me a hard question.

03:46.394 --> 03:48.462
How old will I be
when you die?

03:48.496 --> 03:49.563
Probably 51.

03:51.765 --> 03:54.535
Hey, Douglas, uh, your girls
are measuring my car.

03:54.568 --> 03:55.269
Should I be worried?

03:55.303 --> 03:56.904
With them, yes.

03:56.937 --> 03:59.206
Always yes.

03:59.239 --> 04:02.876
**

04:02.910 --> 04:04.878
I've been cast
as Vince Fontaine.

04:04.912 --> 04:07.014
Who?
The B-list celeb

04:07.047 --> 04:09.082
who judges high school
dance contests for some reason.

04:09.116 --> 04:10.884
I guess to supplement
his income!

04:10.918 --> 04:13.287
Well, who the hell got cast
as Danny Zuko?

04:13.321 --> 04:15.389
I've been cast
as Danny Zuko!

04:16.557 --> 04:18.526
The lead
of the musical "Grease"!

04:18.559 --> 04:19.627
Oh...

04:19.660 --> 04:22.029
I have so many lines, Mom!

04:22.062 --> 04:24.465
And I have to say them!
On a platform!

04:24.498 --> 04:26.166
In front of people!

04:26.199 --> 04:28.035
I think that's called
a stage, honey.

04:28.068 --> 04:30.904
All that matters is that you do
your best and...

04:30.938 --> 04:31.905
have fun?

04:31.939 --> 04:32.940
Fun?!

04:32.973 --> 04:34.375
How can I have fun

04:34.408 --> 04:37.445
when the universe
has totally biffed it?!

04:37.478 --> 04:39.747
Thought you might be
running low.

04:39.780 --> 04:40.514
Mm.

04:40.548 --> 04:42.383
How's Graham?

04:42.416 --> 04:44.552
I just caught him vomiting
mid-hand jive.

04:44.585 --> 04:45.953
So, yeah,
he's a little nervous.

04:45.986 --> 04:46.987
How's Rory?

04:47.020 --> 04:48.989
He's -- He's great.
Yeah.

04:49.022 --> 04:50.891
Unrelated, should we go
introduce ourselves

04:50.924 --> 04:52.526
to the new drama teacher?
Just to...

04:52.560 --> 04:54.428
Just to what?
Bum ourselves out?

04:54.462 --> 04:56.129
Well, no, just to see
what could be done

04:56.163 --> 04:58.566
about this whole
casting boo-boo.

04:58.599 --> 05:00.401
[ Chuckles ] You know, I mean,
I never meddle, bu--

05:00.434 --> 05:01.469
Poppy.
Mm?

05:01.502 --> 05:04.137
Have you ever met
my friend...Poppy?

05:05.573 --> 05:07.875
Okay. Okay.
I meddle occasionally.

05:07.908 --> 05:08.909
Bu--
Occasionally?

05:08.942 --> 05:10.844
You beat up
spelling bee judges.

05:10.878 --> 05:13.447
You blackmailed
the commissioner of T-Ball.

05:13.481 --> 05:15.616
And I still to this day
don't know how Rory,

05:15.649 --> 05:17.951
as a first grader,
gets to edit the yearbook.

05:17.985 --> 05:19.086
He has a vision --

05:19.119 --> 05:20.954
Sensations!
Hmm...

05:20.988 --> 05:22.122
Don't tell him
that's also a condom.

05:22.155 --> 05:23.090
[ Sighs ]

05:23.123 --> 05:24.458
Okay, fine, I meddle.

05:24.492 --> 05:26.159
And no,
Rory's not doing great.

05:26.193 --> 05:27.595
He's a mess.
Okay, look.

05:27.628 --> 05:29.463
What you call
a casting boo-boo,

05:29.497 --> 05:32.165
I call a gross miscarriage
of justice.

05:32.199 --> 05:33.667
Right.
You don't think
I wanna meddle?

05:33.701 --> 05:36.336
I wanna meddle so hard,
it hurts.

05:36.370 --> 05:37.605
But I won't.

05:37.638 --> 05:40.908
Because no matter how hard it is
for me to watch,

05:40.941 --> 05:43.577
I'm just gonna have to accept
the fact that my son,

05:43.611 --> 05:45.278
Graham...

05:45.312 --> 05:47.515
is going to have to carry...
a school play.

05:47.548 --> 05:48.682
Oh, God.

05:48.716 --> 05:49.983
Okay, fine,
so your answer's no.

05:50.017 --> 05:51.318
Fair enough.
We won't meddle.

05:52.520 --> 05:55.022
I won't meddle.

05:55.055 --> 05:56.990
[ Knock on door ]
Mr. Biscuits?

05:57.024 --> 05:59.493
Hmm?
I need to talk to you.

05:59.527 --> 06:01.562
[ British accent ] You know,
Mr. Biscuits was my father.

06:01.595 --> 06:03.631
Please,
call me Dr. Biscuits.

06:03.664 --> 06:04.765
Huh.

06:04.798 --> 06:06.066
Okay.

06:08.602 --> 06:12.139
Why was this horrifying
snake earring under our couch?

06:15.008 --> 06:16.477
Dr. Dewan left it here.

06:16.510 --> 06:18.178
Dr. Dewan was here?
Yes, she was.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.980
With you?
Yes.

06:20.013 --> 06:24.017
Why would my doctor
come to my house to see my dad?

06:24.051 --> 06:25.152
Oh, no.

06:25.185 --> 06:27.621
Am I really, really,
really sick?

06:27.655 --> 06:29.289
No. No, honey.

06:29.322 --> 06:31.091
No, you are not sick.

06:31.124 --> 06:32.526
Then why
was my doctor here?

06:32.560 --> 06:36.096
Because...

06:36.129 --> 06:37.397
you're the opposite
of sick.

06:37.431 --> 06:39.700
Why would she tell you that
in person?

06:39.733 --> 06:41.502
Or at all?

06:41.535 --> 06:43.070
Aren't lots of people
the opposite of sick?

06:43.103 --> 06:45.739
Not as opposite of sick
as you.

06:45.773 --> 06:48.842
Dr. Dewan came to our house
in person

06:48.876 --> 06:52.946
because you are
so the opposite of sick that...

06:52.980 --> 06:54.848
she nominated you
for an award.

06:54.882 --> 06:56.183
And you won!

06:56.216 --> 06:58.251
Sophia Nairobi Cooper,
congratulations!

06:58.285 --> 06:59.386
You're the winner

06:59.419 --> 07:02.990
of the Healthiest Child
in America Award!

07:03.023 --> 07:07.094
Healthiest Child In America
is an award you can win?

07:07.127 --> 07:09.196
Mm-hmm.
Yes!

07:09.229 --> 07:11.632
I'm the healthiest child
in America!

07:11.665 --> 07:13.701
Yay!
Suck it, Gwen!

07:13.734 --> 07:15.936
Gwen's a girl at school who
won't shut up about vitamins.

07:15.969 --> 07:17.571
I know who Gwen is
'cause I'm such a good father!

07:17.605 --> 07:20.541
Yaaaaaaaaaay!Yaaaaaaaaaay!

07:20.574 --> 07:21.942
...aaaaaaaay.

07:27.080 --> 07:28.582
I got your text.
Healthiest Child in
America? I hate it.

07:28.616 --> 07:30.918
But I want to tell you
something. I'm proud of you.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.720
All I've ever wanted
was to make you proud.

07:33.921 --> 07:36.223
But not for this, okay?
I don't lie to Sophie ever.

07:36.256 --> 07:38.091
I can't lie, okay?
I have to come clean.

07:38.125 --> 07:39.292
No, no, no, no.
You never come clean.

07:39.326 --> 07:41.261
You double down.
You double down hard.

07:41.294 --> 07:43.096
Kids, Aunt Gail called.

07:43.130 --> 07:46.634
She did 23andMe, and it turns
out we're not related after all.

07:46.667 --> 07:49.469
I'm just glad my parents
aren't alive to find out.

07:49.503 --> 07:51.705
If they're even
my parents.

07:51.739 --> 07:53.741
No offense to the twins,
but Sophie's smart.

07:53.774 --> 07:56.143
She's bought the lie for now,
but she's gonna figure it out.

07:56.176 --> 07:58.746
Nonsense. She's a child.
Children are dumb.

07:58.779 --> 08:01.549
Daddy, how come the Healthiest
Child in America Award

08:01.582 --> 08:02.950
doesn't have a website?

08:02.983 --> 08:04.952
Are you sure it's real?
What?!

08:04.985 --> 08:06.654
There's no
Healthiest-Child-In-America.com?

08:06.687 --> 08:08.622
No. There's not.

08:08.656 --> 08:10.157
I must have, um --

08:10.190 --> 08:12.860
Forgot how to teach your
daughter to use the Internet?

08:12.893 --> 08:14.427
"Dot com"?

08:14.461 --> 08:17.765
Come on, this is a clear-cut
"dot gov" situation.

08:17.798 --> 08:19.967
The Healthiest Child
in America Awards

08:20.000 --> 08:21.434
are funded
by taxpayers.

08:21.468 --> 08:22.770
Happily, I should add.

08:22.803 --> 08:23.971
My mistake.

08:24.004 --> 08:27.040
I just assumed it came
from the private sector.

08:27.074 --> 08:29.777
So, where am I accepting
my award, Dad?

08:29.810 --> 08:32.212
You mean me? Just 'cause
Douglas is a dad, too, so...

08:32.245 --> 08:33.346
Washington, D.C.

08:33.380 --> 08:34.915
The He-Chas are always

08:34.948 --> 08:36.083
in Washington, D.C.
What he said. In...

08:37.484 --> 08:38.852
We're still
doing this, huh?

08:38.886 --> 08:40.921
All right.
I respect that.

08:42.522 --> 08:43.757
Why would you say
it's in Washington, D.C.?

08:43.791 --> 08:46.026
It's a national award.
Where else would it be held?

08:46.059 --> 08:47.895
She's onto us.
Okay, so you're trapped
in a lie.

08:47.928 --> 08:50.497
You just keep on lying.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.499
Life's a wild ride, huh?

08:52.532 --> 08:53.834
What if I can't
lie my way out of it?

08:53.867 --> 08:55.402
Sophie has learned a lot
from "The Good Wife."

08:55.435 --> 08:56.837
You can. We can.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.471
Yes, she's a smart child,

08:58.505 --> 09:00.574
but even smart children
get bored.

09:00.608 --> 09:03.176
All we have to do is just
keep dragging out the lie

09:03.210 --> 09:04.712
until she loses interest.

09:04.745 --> 09:06.980
We're in a war of attrition,
my friend.

09:07.014 --> 09:08.649
Oh, good.
I'm at war.

09:08.682 --> 09:09.650
With my child.

09:09.683 --> 09:10.651
Yes.

09:12.252 --> 09:15.055
So, long story riveting,
my porridge won.

09:15.088 --> 09:16.824
And that's how I got
my honorary doctorate.

09:16.857 --> 09:17.958
And you are?

09:17.991 --> 09:20.327
Uh, Poppy Banks.
I'm Rory's mother.

09:20.360 --> 09:22.195
Yes, your son
is wildly talented.

09:22.229 --> 09:23.997
Thank you.

09:24.031 --> 09:25.699
But you didn't cast him
as Danny.

09:25.733 --> 09:27.500
Precisely.
Too expected.

09:27.534 --> 09:30.437
You see, Ms. Banks, theater
should never be comfortable.

09:30.470 --> 09:33.907
Theater should never
be safe...anywhere.

09:33.941 --> 09:38.011
But especially -- especially --
here in elementary school.

09:38.045 --> 09:39.579
I couldn't agree more.
Mm.

09:39.613 --> 09:42.515
I mean, a straight-ahead,
down-the-middle "Grease"?

09:42.549 --> 09:44.184
Yawn. [ Laughing ]

09:44.217 --> 09:45.686
And that's
not the Biscuits way.

09:45.719 --> 09:46.754
Ah, you've read my book.

09:46.787 --> 09:48.255
Of course.

09:48.288 --> 09:50.357
You know what I'd do
if I had my copy

09:50.390 --> 09:51.659
o-of...

09:51.692 --> 09:52.660
"Daddy Never Clapped."

09:52.693 --> 09:53.894
Yes.

09:53.927 --> 09:56.529
Oh, I would turn
to chapter...

09:56.563 --> 09:58.098
125.

09:58.131 --> 10:00.734
"Sleep with Caution All You
Like, But Always Marry Danger."

10:00.768 --> 10:01.969
And I'd say...

10:03.570 --> 10:06.406
...What about expanding
the role of Vince Fontaine?

10:06.439 --> 10:08.876
Ooh.

10:08.909 --> 10:12.579
"Grease" as seen through
the lens of Rydell High's

10:12.612 --> 10:15.448
first African-American
celebrity dance contest judge.

10:15.482 --> 10:17.250
Mm.

10:17.284 --> 10:20.253
**

10:20.287 --> 10:21.221
What?! How the --

10:23.556 --> 10:24.725
They're seven!

10:24.758 --> 10:26.794
How would you like
for your car

10:26.827 --> 10:29.296
to become
the Greased Lightnin'?

10:29.329 --> 10:31.398
You want my car
for your play?

10:31.431 --> 10:33.233
Aw,
look who came to class.

10:33.266 --> 10:34.835
Don't you want
a cool car?

10:34.868 --> 10:36.569
Sure,
but look at this heap.

10:36.603 --> 10:38.238
It'll never be
Greased Lightnin'.

10:38.271 --> 10:40.440
This car could have
AC and heating.

10:40.473 --> 10:41.441
[ Note blares ]

10:41.474 --> 10:42.776
Zero leaking.

10:42.810 --> 10:43.643
[ Note blares ]

10:43.677 --> 10:46.313
Both:
Upholstered seating.

10:46.346 --> 10:49.649
[ Note blares ]
This car could be
Greased Lightnin'?

10:49.683 --> 10:50.984
**

10:51.018 --> 10:52.686
* We'll get
some overhead lifters *

10:52.720 --> 10:54.654
* And four barrel quads,
oh, yeah *

10:54.688 --> 10:56.489
* Keep talkin',
whoa, keep talkin' *

10:56.523 --> 10:58.625
* With a four-speed
on the floor *

10:58.658 --> 11:00.728
* They'll be waiting
at the door, Greased Lightnin' *

11:00.761 --> 11:03.496
* Go, go, go,
go-go-go-go-go-go-go-go *

11:03.530 --> 11:05.165
* Go, Greased Lightnin'

11:05.198 --> 11:06.834
* You're burnin' up
the quarter mile *

11:06.867 --> 11:09.136
* Greased Lightnin',
go, Greased Lightnin' *

11:09.169 --> 11:11.604
* You are supreme,
the chicks'll scream *
* Uh-huh, uh-huh

11:11.638 --> 11:14.141
* For Greased Lightnin', yeah
* Go, go, go

11:14.174 --> 11:15.809
* Go-go-go-go-go-go-go-go

11:15.843 --> 11:19.179
* Yeah, I said go,
Greased Lightnin', go *

11:19.212 --> 11:21.681
* I said go, you crazy car

11:21.715 --> 11:23.851
* I said Greasy Lightning,
Greasy Thunder *

11:23.884 --> 11:26.419
* Sca-ba-doo-bow-boo-ba

11:26.453 --> 11:28.521
Why did Vince Fontaine
stop the dance contest

11:28.555 --> 11:29.990
to sing
"Greased Lightnin'"?

11:30.023 --> 11:32.359
And who invited him
to the girls' sleepover?

11:32.392 --> 11:34.061
He pierced Sandy's ears!

11:35.362 --> 11:37.164
You totally meddled!

11:37.197 --> 11:38.866
Okay, yes, I meddled

11:38.899 --> 11:40.667
so that Graham
could have less lines.

11:40.700 --> 11:42.402
I thought you'd be happy.
Happy?

11:42.435 --> 11:44.104
Please, I'm thrilled
Graham has less lines.

11:44.137 --> 11:46.173
But that's me
just being selfish.

11:46.206 --> 11:47.640
What if it would be
a good thing

11:47.674 --> 11:49.009
for Graham to be a lead
in the play?

11:49.042 --> 11:51.578
What if, I don't know, it got
him out of his comfort zone?

11:51.611 --> 11:54.614
What if he is one
of the great actors of our time?

11:54.647 --> 11:58.118
Help! The grease in my hair
is attracting bees! Aah!

11:58.151 --> 12:01.221
Don't pretend that you meddled
on Graham's behalf.

12:01.254 --> 12:03.957
You've never done it before,
and he struggles all the time.

12:03.991 --> 12:05.692
Struggling is his brand.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.494
You rewrote "Grease"

12:07.527 --> 12:09.562
because you couldn't stand
to see Rory struggle.

12:09.596 --> 12:11.498
[ Gasps ]
I did not rewrite "Grease."

12:11.531 --> 12:13.300
A meddler operates
in the shadows.

12:13.333 --> 12:15.535
All I did was ask Biscuits
if he could explore the idea

12:15.568 --> 12:17.004
of expanding
the Fontaine-i-verse!

12:17.037 --> 12:19.139
What the hell
is Biscuits?!

12:19.172 --> 12:21.741
I the hell am Biscuits!

12:21.775 --> 12:23.210
Take five, everyone!

12:25.813 --> 12:27.347
Everyone but you two.

12:29.116 --> 12:30.183
So, that's
the new drama teacher?

12:30.217 --> 12:31.484
Yeah, that's Biscuits.

12:31.518 --> 12:32.752
Ohhh.

12:32.786 --> 12:35.588
Biscuits is a person.

12:35.622 --> 12:38.358
And that's why,
if we are forced to have them,

12:38.391 --> 12:40.060
the 50th Annual He-Chas

12:40.093 --> 12:43.330
will be the crown jewel
of the D.C. banquet season.

12:43.363 --> 12:44.965
Now, I have some broadsheets
in the car.

12:44.998 --> 12:46.266
Where do you keep
your easel?

12:46.299 --> 12:47.100
Where don't I
keep my easel?

12:48.802 --> 12:50.437
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:52.439 --> 12:53.773
Hey!
Hey.

12:53.807 --> 12:55.775
Uh, what are you
doing here?

12:55.809 --> 12:57.610
You texted me
to come over.

12:57.644 --> 12:59.446
No, I didn't.
How could I have texted you?

12:59.479 --> 13:01.414
I don't even know
where my phone is.

13:01.448 --> 13:03.984
Your passcode
is Al Roker's birthday?

13:04.017 --> 13:05.618
Pretty weak, Dad.

13:05.652 --> 13:07.921
Dr. Dewan.
Please, come in.

13:07.955 --> 13:11.558
There's much to discuss.

13:11.591 --> 13:14.094
**

13:14.127 --> 13:15.728
And so it begins.

13:20.067 --> 13:21.634
Okay, I know you only like
being around sick kids --

13:21.668 --> 13:22.903
Clients.
So weird that you call them
that, but okay, fine.

13:22.936 --> 13:25.272
Your client, Sophie,
my daughter, is not sick.

13:25.305 --> 13:27.340
Gross.
Then what am I doing here?

13:27.374 --> 13:28.508
I need you to help me
outsmart her, okay?

13:28.541 --> 13:29.642
I can't let her
find out about you.

13:29.676 --> 13:31.912
Oh, God. I told you
to just tell her.

13:31.945 --> 13:34.114
Well, we are past that,
and if she finds out I'm lying,

13:34.147 --> 13:36.149
I'm gonna have to spend
all my time trying to
regain her trust,

13:36.183 --> 13:38.751
and I will not have time
to bed you.

13:38.785 --> 13:40.087
And you know
how well I do that.

13:40.120 --> 13:42.422
I do. Nothing has
surprised me more.

13:42.455 --> 13:43.924
All right,
what do you need me to do?

13:43.957 --> 13:45.893
Memorize this --
you nominated Sophie

13:45.926 --> 13:47.694
for The Healthiest Child
in America Award,

13:47.727 --> 13:49.396
and the ceremony's in
Washington, D.C.'s Ritz-Carlton.

13:49.429 --> 13:50.730
The appetizers
are in the lobby,

13:50.763 --> 13:52.199
and the banquet's
in the Crescent Room. Got it?

13:52.232 --> 13:53.566
Got it.
Just one question.

13:54.968 --> 13:56.636
Is there
a vegetarian option?

13:56.669 --> 13:58.138
Ohh, you...

13:58.171 --> 13:59.940
[ Giggles ]
[ Moans ]

13:59.973 --> 14:01.708
I don't know. I'll have to
check with Douglas. Come on.

14:01.741 --> 14:03.610
[ Sighs ]

14:03.643 --> 14:06.713
**

14:06.746 --> 14:08.781
You sit here, Dr. Dewan.

14:08.815 --> 14:11.084
[ Clears throat ]

14:12.752 --> 14:16.456
Dr. Dewan, am I
the healthiest child in America?

14:16.489 --> 14:19.826
I wouldn't have nominated you
if you weren't. Congratulations.

14:19.859 --> 14:22.062
[ Whispering ]
You got one hell of a woman
on your hands here.

14:22.095 --> 14:23.663
Will I be expected
to change gowns

14:23.696 --> 14:25.265
between appetizers
in the Crescent Room

14:25.298 --> 14:26.633
and the banquet
in the lobby?

14:26.666 --> 14:28.301
Sorry, appetizers
are in the lobby

14:28.335 --> 14:30.403
and the banquet
is in the Crescent Room.

14:30.437 --> 14:32.772
And I'm sure
that one gown will be plenty.

14:32.805 --> 14:34.807
Exquisitely handled.
Frankly, she's too good for you.

14:34.841 --> 14:36.743
[ Scoffs ]
Just one more question.

14:36.776 --> 14:38.311
There's been rumors
going around

14:38.345 --> 14:40.380
saying that the banquet
might be rescheduled.

14:40.413 --> 14:41.581
Is that true?

14:41.614 --> 14:42.983
Uh...um...

14:43.016 --> 14:44.184
A-A ru-- A rumor?

14:44.217 --> 14:46.353
Uh, that's news to me.

14:46.386 --> 14:48.155
That's right, Sophie.
The rumors are true.

14:48.188 --> 14:50.057
The banquet
is rescheduled.

14:50.090 --> 14:51.224
For when?
For tonight.

14:52.259 --> 14:53.826
Oh, this is
gonna be fun.

14:53.860 --> 14:55.862
Bring it.

14:55.895 --> 14:57.830
When was the banquet
originally scheduled for?

14:57.864 --> 14:58.565
Christmas Eve.

14:58.598 --> 15:00.200
Why is it
being rescheduled?

15:00.233 --> 15:02.135
Because there's a forecast
for inclement weather.

15:02.169 --> 15:03.503
But it's an indoor banquet.

15:03.536 --> 15:06.339
Main course indoors,
dessert course outdoors.

15:06.373 --> 15:08.041
What's the dessert course?
Ice cream bar.

15:08.075 --> 15:09.709
Outdoor ice cream
in December?

15:09.742 --> 15:11.311
Coats provided.

15:11.344 --> 15:13.213
How late will it go?
All night long, baby.

15:13.246 --> 15:15.448
Washington, D.C.,
has a 24-hour, year-round,

15:15.482 --> 15:16.516
outdoor ice-cream venue?

15:16.549 --> 15:17.184
You heard me.

15:17.217 --> 15:18.751
What's it called?

15:19.953 --> 15:22.055
Event-Boyz Entertainment
presents

15:22.089 --> 15:24.224
Ice Cream Under The Stars

15:24.257 --> 15:26.659
at Arlington
National Cemetery.

15:26.693 --> 15:28.795
Okay, you know what? Stop, stop!
I can't take it anymore.

15:28.828 --> 15:30.297
Sophie...

15:30.330 --> 15:31.664
you are not
the healthiest child in America.

15:31.698 --> 15:33.266
Duh.

15:33.300 --> 15:34.901
Perhaps
in an unofficial capacity --

15:34.934 --> 15:36.169
She's not.
I mean, sure, she's healthy,

15:36.203 --> 15:37.237
but let's just say
I'm not in love

15:37.270 --> 15:39.606
with the ammonia levels
in her urine.

15:39.639 --> 15:40.907
Honey...

15:40.940 --> 15:43.843
Dr. Dewan and I
are seeing each other.

15:45.412 --> 15:48.281
And I lied to you
about a fake banquet

15:48.315 --> 15:50.517
because I was scared
to tell you the truth.

15:50.550 --> 15:52.052
I'm sorry.

15:52.085 --> 15:55.422
And I'm sorry that your dad
suffers from a rare disorder

15:55.455 --> 15:59.326
that makes him think
real banquets are actually fake.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.162
What's it called?

16:04.097 --> 16:07.300
Hypo-banquetitis-phrenia...

16:07.334 --> 16:09.236
Type...B.

16:09.269 --> 16:10.137
Fine!

16:10.170 --> 16:12.505
You win!
There's no banquet!

16:12.539 --> 16:14.907
**

16:14.941 --> 16:16.109
Places.

16:16.143 --> 16:17.810
Mr. Biscuits,
I'm not sure why --

16:17.844 --> 16:20.380
Dr. Biscuits. Or else he'll do
an hour on the Porridge Fair.

16:20.413 --> 16:22.749
You are here because
you interrupted rehearsal

16:22.782 --> 16:24.551
and you made a mockery

16:24.584 --> 16:27.354
of everything
the cast of "Winter Homecoming:

16:27.387 --> 16:31.124
Vince Fontaine's Grease Legacy,
Part One" holds dear.

16:31.158 --> 16:33.360
And I would like
to know why.

16:33.393 --> 16:34.761
Fair enough.
You know what?

16:34.794 --> 16:36.663
We'll hash it out at home
and get back to you.

16:36.696 --> 16:38.498
Ah!
This is your home now.

16:38.531 --> 16:40.567
A chapel where two friends

16:40.600 --> 16:43.570
can bridge the rift
that has grown between them.

16:43.603 --> 16:45.138
In the theater, we live,

16:45.172 --> 16:46.806
we uncover,

16:46.839 --> 16:48.007
and we heal.

16:49.309 --> 16:51.944
O-O-kay. I-I didn't understand
m-most of that.

16:51.978 --> 16:53.113
None of us understand
any of it!

16:53.146 --> 16:55.048
And lights up on...

16:56.916 --> 16:58.051
Oh, me?

17:00.187 --> 17:01.521
Uh...[ Sighs ]

17:01.554 --> 17:02.689
[ Scoffs ]

17:02.722 --> 17:03.690
I think --

17:03.723 --> 17:05.392
Think as a smoker.

17:07.627 --> 17:09.329
All right, look,
speaking for myself,

17:09.362 --> 17:10.530
I just wanted to s--
Biscuits: Unh-unh!

17:10.563 --> 17:12.099
No one speaks
for themselves

17:12.132 --> 17:14.234
unless they're wounded.

17:14.267 --> 17:15.468
Oh.

17:15.502 --> 17:17.104
And limp.

17:21.141 --> 17:22.709
I know
I shouldn't meddle,

17:22.742 --> 17:24.711
but there are just so many times
that I can't protect Rory.

17:24.744 --> 17:26.012
So when I can, I do.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.081
Can I take that again?
Yes.

17:28.115 --> 17:31.484
So when I can, I do!

17:31.518 --> 17:33.153
Poppy, you are
a terrible scene partner.

17:33.186 --> 17:34.421
You're not even
looking at me.

17:34.454 --> 17:38.291
I know you are terrified
to see your kid fail,

17:38.325 --> 17:39.692
but kids need to fail.

17:39.726 --> 17:40.693
It's good for them.

17:40.727 --> 17:42.529
And coming from someone

17:42.562 --> 17:45.232
who sees their kid fail
all the time,

17:45.265 --> 17:47.434
believe me,
you get used to it.

17:47.467 --> 17:48.835
Really.

17:51.204 --> 17:52.839
And curtain.

17:52.872 --> 17:57.009
I can only pray that your sons
can create such truth on stage.

17:57.043 --> 17:58.345
And that you have
a loved one

17:58.378 --> 18:00.413
that can attend
and record it for you.

18:00.447 --> 18:02.949
Because the punishment
for disrupting rehearsal

18:02.982 --> 18:04.317
is banishment
from the theater.

18:04.351 --> 18:05.318
Forever.

18:05.352 --> 18:06.085
[ Gasps ]

18:07.487 --> 18:08.921
I'm joking!
[ Chuckles ]

18:08.955 --> 18:10.490
Just for this play.

18:10.523 --> 18:13.326
Which, by the way,
is just "Grease," after all.

18:13.360 --> 18:17.096
I'm saving "Winter Homecoming:
V.F.G.L. One" for summer stock,

18:17.130 --> 18:18.931
where the nudity
won't be watered down.

18:18.965 --> 18:21.768
**

18:21.801 --> 18:23.703
I'm really sorry I lied.

18:23.736 --> 18:26.439
And I'm sorry for seeing through
your lie, calling your bluff,

18:26.473 --> 18:28.441
and forcing you
to be honest with me.

18:28.475 --> 18:30.177
So, I guess
we both made mistakes.

18:30.210 --> 18:32.279
Sophie,
you know that you are

18:32.312 --> 18:34.281
the most important person
in the world to me, right?

18:34.314 --> 18:37.584
And I was just scared that
if I started dating someone,

18:37.617 --> 18:39.319
you might worry
that that's not true anymore.

18:39.352 --> 18:40.753
I get it.

18:40.787 --> 18:43.690
Mom's far away, and it's been
just you and me for --

18:43.723 --> 18:44.924
That's all I needed to hear.
I'll never date again.

18:44.957 --> 18:46.293
No, no.
I want you to.

18:46.326 --> 18:48.561
It'll be weird
sharing you with someone,

18:48.595 --> 18:50.297
but also maybe good?

18:50.330 --> 18:51.331
Hmm.

18:51.364 --> 18:52.765
You can be a lot, Dad.

18:52.799 --> 18:54.133
Imagine what it's like
being me.

18:54.167 --> 18:55.468
At least you get a break.

18:55.502 --> 18:57.270
Listen, I won't always
tell you everything

18:57.304 --> 18:58.438
if I think
it's for your own good,

18:58.471 --> 19:01.541
but I promise you,
I will never lie to you.

19:01.574 --> 19:04.010
And if you ever have
any questions, I'm always here.

19:05.812 --> 19:08.215
Have you and Dr. Dewan
held hands?

19:08.248 --> 19:10.016
Oh, we're doing questions now.
Okay, great.

19:10.049 --> 19:11.418
Yes, we've held hands.

19:11.451 --> 19:13.286
Does it sometimes feel like
you're from Mars

19:13.320 --> 19:15.255
and she's from Venus?
Constantly.

19:15.288 --> 19:16.423
What were you guys doing
that mashed her earring

19:16.456 --> 19:18.225
so far into the carpet?

19:18.258 --> 19:20.293
And we've already arrived
at something I won't tell
you for your own good.

19:20.327 --> 19:21.761
Sorry.
Don't be.

19:21.794 --> 19:24.130
When it's for your own good,
I don't tell you everything.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.898
Great.
I'm glad about that.

19:25.932 --> 19:27.634
That's totally healthy.

19:30.370 --> 19:31.771
**

19:31.804 --> 19:33.340
[ Toy squeaks ]

19:33.373 --> 19:38.110
**

19:38.144 --> 19:39.512
This is boring.

19:40.780 --> 19:42.782
Okay, so,
I just saw this play

19:42.815 --> 19:44.551
performed with
all the characters.

19:44.584 --> 19:47.787
Now we're gonna watch it again
with just two characters? Why?

19:47.820 --> 19:50.156
Because Angie and I were banned
from the official premiere.

19:50.189 --> 19:52.225
But not the unauthorized,
two-man encore,

19:52.259 --> 19:54.627
which leaves
15 roles uncast.

19:54.661 --> 19:56.296
So could be
some dead spots.

19:56.329 --> 19:58.631
There won't be any. 'Cause
my car steals every scene.

19:58.665 --> 19:59.866
Yeah, yeah.

19:59.899 --> 20:01.000
Oh, shh-shh-shh!
Here she comes.

20:02.735 --> 20:03.903
[ Gasps ]

20:09.709 --> 20:11.711
Hey, you guys,
what's shakin'?

20:13.346 --> 20:16.316
Well, I spent most of my time
down at the beach.

20:17.750 --> 20:20.052
Is that all
you ever think about, Sonny?

20:21.388 --> 20:22.555
[ Giggles ]

20:22.589 --> 20:23.990
[ Whispering ]
I'm lost.

20:24.023 --> 20:25.492
Has Danny
gone crazy?

20:25.525 --> 20:27.494
Dude, I'm watching
the same play you are.

20:27.527 --> 20:28.928
**

20:33.533 --> 20:34.667
So, you got the word, huh?
Ease off, Kenickie.

20:34.701 --> 20:36.336
[ Breathing heavily ]

20:36.369 --> 20:37.236
Stop it!

20:38.438 --> 20:40.172
I'm sorry you had to see me lose

20:40.206 --> 20:42.208
my greatest parenting gift
like that.

20:42.241 --> 20:43.810
I'm certain your ability
to lie to children

20:43.843 --> 20:45.211
will come back eventually.

20:45.244 --> 20:46.212
Yeah, but what if --

20:46.245 --> 20:49.015
what if it doesn't?

20:49.048 --> 20:50.950
Oh, Sandy,

20:50.983 --> 20:52.719
you're something else.

20:52.752 --> 20:54.220
[ Smooches ]

20:54.253 --> 20:58.425
**

